# Pre-push Hook Rules

## Branch Protection
- Prevent direct pushes to main/master branch
- Require pull requests for protected branches
- Ensure branch naming conventions are followed
- Check for up-to-date branch with remote

## Code Quality Gates
- All tests must pass
- Code coverage must meet minimum threshold (80%)
- No linting errors allowed
- Build must complete successfully

## Security Validation
- Run security vulnerability scan
- Check for exposed secrets one final time
- Validate dependencies for known vulnerabilities
- Ensure no sensitive files in commit history

## CI/CD Checks
- Verify CI configuration is valid
- Check that all required CI checks are defined
- Ensure deployment scripts are tested
- Validate environment configurations

## Large File Prevention
- Block files larger than 100MB
- Warn for files larger than 50MB
- Check total repository size limits
- Validate no binary artifacts in source

## Commit Verification
- Ensure commits are signed (if required)
- Validate commit authors
- Check for fixup/squash commits
- Verify no merge commits (if using rebase workflow)

## Documentation Requirements
- Changelog must be updated for releases
- API documentation must be current
- README must reflect current state
- Migration guides for breaking changes

## Remote Validation
- Check remote repository accessibility
- Verify push permissions
- Ensure remote branch exists
- Validate no force push to protected branches